{"id":"0910.4127","submitter":"Yuri Genenko","authors":"Yu.A. Genenko, S.V. Yampolskii, C. Melzer, K. Stegmaier, H. von\n  Seggern","title":"Charge carrier injection into insulating media: single-particle versus\n  mean-field approach","comments":"32 pages, 9 figures; revised version accepted to PRB","journal-ref":"Physical Review B 81, 125310 (2010)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.81.125310","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mtrl-sci","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Self-consistent, mean-field description of charge injection into a dielectric\nmedium is modified to account for discreteness of charge carriers. The improved\nscheme includes both the Schottky barrier lowering due to the individual image\ncharge and the barrier change due to the field penetration into the injecting\nelectrode that ensures validity of the model at both high and low injection\nrates including the barrier dominated and the space-charge dominated regimes.\nComparison of the theory with experiment on an unipolar ITO/PPV/Au-device is\npresented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Oct 2009 15:51:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Dec 2009 11:01:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 22 Jan 2010 14:05:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-03-11"}
